Description:
Ballistics of 115x728R 3UBM9 round, with the 3BM21 "Zastup" APFSDS-T projectile, fired from the U-5TS tank gun (GRAU index 2A20) chiefly employed on the T-62 tank. Projectile is of tungsten-carbide core construction and equipeed with ballistic cap. Developed persuant to directive issued in 1972, alongside Zakolka (125mm), Kalach (100mm), Izomer (100mm). Adopted in 1977-1979, although production began in 1975-1976. Loads 8 kg of 12/7 V/A grains. Variation of 3UBM9 performance due to temperature is given in АРТИЛЛЕРИЙСКИЕ МЕТАТЕЛЬНЫЕ ЗАРЯДЫ:
T.  M.V. P.mcp 
°C  m/s  kgf/cm² MPa 
-40 1550 3060
+15 1600 4100    450
+40 1620 4650
Pressure is taken as copper crusher gauge values and converted via 1.12 x 0.098 to piezo value in MPa.
